{"TopicId":160570,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"This terrain bug has been here for nearly three years now.","CreatedByName":"Secret Agent Kirrim","CreatedById":98579,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-13T07:58:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Secret Agent Kirrim","CreatedById":98579,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-13T07:58:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis little clip has been sitting here for a long time now without anyone noticing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mkBmZrv.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mkBmZrv.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m surprised that nobody has noticed this as of late.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCo-ordinates:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n0-7-0 South\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n74-48-41 West\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-13T07:59:50Z\u0022 title=\u002205/13/2017 07:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 13, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Secret Agent Kirrim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Overland","CreatedById":119812,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-13T08:30:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nas a full time driver - sadly if it was just that little crack i\u0027d be happy as all kerbinkind..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwith each version we have got more and more cracks.. to the point that now currently they span across kerbin in repeated diamond shapes mostly where terrain changed elevation\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBack in 0.90 you could only see them with scattermod turned on at the right time of day..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthese days.. they\u0027re everywhere and visible as day.. its become more and more evident recently and im sure theres a bug tracker about it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits extremely disheartening too. .as they arnt just graphic errors but actual terrain gaps.. I tend to blow the air horns as I cross one in a train.. adds a little fun.. but the reality of it is.. its not nice.. theres nothing nice about this at all\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthey span all of kerbin now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hUmf8en.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/hUmf8en.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nterrain used to be smooth rolling hills with some extremes .. part of the optimisation things got a little.. jagged.. I think this makes it more apparent\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for making the thread, its a known issue but someone has to push for it to be seen\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrees also have a shadow problem these days its fixed in 1.29.. but with so many mods broken its not going to be a good change\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-13T08:34:13Z\u0022 title=\u002205/13/2017 08:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 13, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Overland\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wasml","CreatedById":120438,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-14T16:35:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know I\u0027ve popped tires and flipped rovers on these - one in particular near the mountains west of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E (Was doing about 20m/s) gave me considerable air time before the remains of the rover hit the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-14T18:37:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomewhere after release of 1.2 SQUAD asked the community to look for terrain seams all around the Kerbol system, and they were fixing them since then. Most of the holes should be fixed by now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-14T18:49:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom February 10 of this year:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003EInvestigations continue on the terrain seams but we have made some progress. We want to give\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cb style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003Especial thanks\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eto swjr-swis, klgraham1013, and KroShan for submitting the saves. All of the saves are helping us figure out what the problem is and will give us lots of places to test the fixes.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/156278-ksp-weekly-a-short-briefing/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheRagingIrishman","CreatedById":165004,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-15T18:40:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom April 25th of this year\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003EYou would be pleased to know then that the terrain has been fixed in the pre release, and was explained in the KSP Weekly\u0027s as an issue related to floating point changes made in the game engine.\u00A0vertex overlap had nothing to do with it. --JPLRepo\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/developerarticles.html/who-needs-a-level-runway-anyway-r204/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2556\u0026amp;embedComment=2556\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-15T18:43:45Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2017 06:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by TheRagingIrishman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"V7 Aerospace","CreatedById":156062,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-15T22:09:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223055143\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160570\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494664259\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119812\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Overland\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 13 May 2017 at 9:30 AM, Overland said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-snip-\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need to bring this to the attention of more people!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMake trains great again!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DeltaDizzy","CreatedById":150755,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-15T22:39:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI only noticed when it ruined my rover deployer/boat launch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Moose In Your House","CreatedById":177101,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-15T23:05:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223055136\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160570\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494662288\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298579\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Secret Agent Kirrim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E5\u200E/\u200E13\u200E/\u200E2017 at 0:58 AM, Secret Agent Kirrim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis little clip has been sitting here for a long time now without anyone noticing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mkBmZrv.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mkBmZrv.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/mkBmZrv.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m surprised that nobody has noticed this as of late.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCo-ordinates:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n0-7-0 South\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n74-48-41 West\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s strange, I went to the \u003Cb\u003ECoordinates and found no terrain glitches, But I did find some on the runway.\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/qwoqlTK\u0022 style=\u0022height:428px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-15T23:07:17Z\u0022 title=\u002205/15/2017 11:07  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 15, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by The Moose In Your House\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-15T23:17:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are still finding terrain glitches in the latest 1.2.9 prerelease please raise bug reports on the prerelease tracker with coordinates or save files. Also the runways as in QA testing we have not discovered any issues particularly with runways but also terrain. Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-15T23:45:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese\u00A0were fixed last I played 1.2.9. \u00A0I\u0027m hopeful they\u0027re gone in 1.3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-16T11:53:52Z\u0022 title=\u002205/16/2017 11:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 16, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by klgraham1013\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-16T03:51:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA lot of those terrain seam issues can be solved by lowering suspension damper strength to half of standard, or even lower. Experiment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SchwinnTropius","CreatedById":165170,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-16T04:41:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223058087\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160570\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494906700\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250750\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Azimech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, Azimech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA lot of those terrain seam issues can be solved by lowering suspension damper strength to half of standard, or even lower. Experiment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo damper set to 1.75 will probably be too high for those seams?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-16T06:04:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223058106\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160570\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494909685\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165170\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SchwinnTropius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, SchwinnTropius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo damper set to 1.75 will probably be too high for those seams?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsually I set them to 0.5 and experiment from there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Overland","CreatedById":119812,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-16T07:09:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDampeners dont work on trains..its the enemy.. That said, 4432 and her high speed sistertrain 705 never had a problem crossing one with M1 modified wheels\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStrangely enough what did was tank tracks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood to see its fixed in 1.29\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow to get modual manager to catch up \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}